{
    "type": "refactor",
    "subject": "Refactor ScriptRunner to use Bean Scripting Framework (BSF)",
    "body": "This commit refactors the ScriptRunner class to use the Bean Scripting Framework (BSF) in Java. The changes include replacing the line "manager.declareBean(key, value, value.getClass());" with lines "if (value != null) {
manager.declareBean(key, value, value.getClass());
} else {
// bsf uses a hashtable to store values
// so cannot declarebean with a null value
// so need to remove any bean of this name as
// that bean should not be visible
manager.undeclareBean(key);
}" in line 142.The method public void executeScript(String execName) throws BuildException is modified by this git diff.- The addition of "manager.declareBean(key, value, value.getClass());" after line 12 will declare a bean with the key and value from the beans map.- The addition of "} else {" after line 13 will add an else block to handle the case when the value is null.- The addition of "" after line 14 will add a comment.- The addition of "" after line 15 will add a comment.- The addition of "" after line 16 will add a comment.- The addition of "" after line 17 will add a comment.- The addition of "manager.undeclareBean(key);" after line 18 will undeclare the bean with the key."
}

