    "body": "The changes in this commit are related to the TestFramework class. The main method of the TestFramework class is responsible for starting a Mesos scheduler driver and then terminating it. To ensure that the SchedulerDriver teardown is complete before the JVM starts running native object destructors after System.exit() is called, a sleep statement has been added after line 271 of the main method.\n\nThe reason for adding this change is that some platforms may not always terminate all tasks associated with a Mesos scheduler driver when System.exit() is called, resulting in native object destructors being run prematurely.\n\nTo prevent this issue, a sleep statement has been added to ensure that all tasks associated with the SchedulerDriver have completed their teardown before the JVM exits."
