{
    "type": "refactor",
    "subject": "Add @Lob annotation to applicationCertificates field in Client class",
    "body": "The `Client` class is a database entity representing a registered third-party client application. The `applicationCertificates` field is a collection of strings that represents the client's application certificates. This commit adds the `@Lob` annotation to this field, which changes the type of elements in the list from String to Blob (Binary Large Object). This means that the application certificates will be stored as binary data instead of text data.\n\nThis change is necessary because storing large amounts of binary data such as images or videos in text format can be expensive and slow down database operations. Using Blob types allows for more efficient storage and retrieval of large binary data."
}

